{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "25", "m": "04", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "07", "M": "00", "S": "10"}}, "news": [{"title": "Property registration values to go up from May first week in Telangana", "para": "The state government will revise property registration values from early May, ending a year-long deferral. The Hyderabad Industrial Land Transformation (HILT) Policy, allowing landowners to change land use for a fee, will also be implemented. These moves aim to boost resource mobilization and industrial transformation, with consultations planned for industrial associations.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/telangana-property-registration-values-set-to-increase-from-may-as-govt-revives-hilt-policy/130507791?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-26834/130507791.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Telangana fire department holds meeting with builders on proposed amendments to fire services act", "para": "Telangana Fire Department officials met with builders and developers to discuss proposed amendments to the Fire Services Act, 1999. The revisions aim to update regulations for modern urban infrastructure risks, enhance safety, and extend enforcement to buildings below 15 meters. This consultation is part of a process to strengthen fire safety and simplify compliance.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/telangana-fire-department-engages-builders-in-key-fire-safety-regulation-overhaul/130507760?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-84072/130507760.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Kanpur development body board decides to reduce cost of 5,600 unsold flats", "para": "Kanpur Development Authority has decided to lower prices on 5,600 unsold flats. These flats will now be available at 2018 rates, offering significant discounts. The authority also passed a substantial budget for development projects in the current financial year. New infrastructure like a bus stand and a super-speciality hospital are planned.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/kanpur-development-authority-cuts-prices-on-5600-unsold-flats/130507672?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-33546/130507672.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}]}